n39\t| # | source | id | severity | exploitable | location | disposition |\n40\t|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n41\t| 1 | osv | GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g | Medium (CVSS 6.8) | no | `poetry.lock` → `pytest@8.3.4` | action-required |\n42\t| 2 | osv | PYSEC-2026-1845 | Medium (CVSS 6.8) | no | `poetry.lock` → `pytest@8.3.4` | action-required |\n43\t| 3 | manual-6d | RLS backstop inert without FORCE (`quotas`) | Medium | no | `alembic/versions/0003_create_quotas_and_api_key_scope.py:54` | fixed |\n44\t| 4 | manual-6d | RLS backstop inert without FORCE (`events`, `usage_rollup`) | Medium | no | `alembic/versions/0001_*.py:66`, `0002_*.py:67` | reported-only |\n45\t| 5 | semgrep | github-actions-mutable-action-tag | Warning | no | `.github/workflows/pipeline-ci.yml:54` | reported-only |\n46\t| 6 | semgrep | github-actions-mutable-action-tag | Warning | no | `.github/workflows/pipeline-ci.yml:85` | reported-only |\n47\t| 7 | semgrep | dangerous-subprocess-use-tainted-env-args | Error (false positive) | no | `tests/integration/test_perf_k6_load.py:139` | reported-only |\n48\t| 8 | semgrep | dangerous-subprocess-use-tainted-env-args | Error (false positive) | no | `tests/integration/test_perf_k6_load.py:290` | reported-only |\n49\t| 9 | semgrep | avoid-sqlalchemy-text | Error (false positive) | no | `tests/integration/test_quota_migration.py:73` | reported-only |\n50\t\n51\t`total_findings = 9` (2 osv + 2 manual-6d + 5 semgrep). Gitleaks(0 in-scope) + ASVS-SAST(0) + lockfile(0)\n52\tcontribute no rows. `critical_count = 0` after remediation; `fixed_count = 1` (#3); `warning_count = 8`\n53\t(all remaining rows are advisory/non-blocking — see per-item rationale).\n54\t\n55\t## Semgrep triage (rows 5–9)\n56\t\n57\t- **#5 / #6 — `github-actions-mutable-action-tag` (WARNING, real).** Two CI steps in\n58\t  `pipeline-ci.yml` reference a mutable `@vN` tag rather than a pinned commit SHA — a supply-chain\n59\t  hygiene finding (a tag can be silently repointed). WARNING severity → advisory, non-blocking.\n60\t  Not auto-fixed (pinning third-party action SHAs is a CI-ownership decision). Recommend pinning to\n61\t  full-length commit SHAs.\n62\t- **#7 / #8 — `dangerous-subprocess-use-tainted-env-args` (ERROR, false positive).**\n63\t  `test_perf_k6_load.py:139,290` launch uvicorn for a load test via **list-form** `subprocess.Popen`\n64\t  (`[sys.executable, \"-m\", \"uvicorn\", ...]`, **no `shell=True`**). The only interpolated tokens are\n65\t  `str(port)` and `str(workers)`, both internal `int()`-coerced values — there is no shell and no\n66\t  argv-splitting, so no command-injection vector exists. Test-harness code, not deployed. Not\n67\t  exploitable → not a blocking critical.\n68\t- **#9 — `avoid-sqlalchemy-text` (ERROR, false positive).** `test_quota_migration.py:73` builds an\n69\t  f-string into `text()`, but the interpolated `columns`/`values` are **static literals** assembled\n70\t  in-function (`\"key_id, secret_hash, label, rate_limit_per_sec\"` / `\":key_id, :hash, …\"`); every\n71\t  actual value, including `scope`, is passed as a **bound parameter** in `params`. No\n72\t  user-controlled interpolation reaches the SQL string. Not exploitable → not a blocking critical.\n73\t\n74\tThe three ERROR rows are recorded with `exploitable: no` and are **not** counted in `critical_count`\n75\t(step-7 exploitability judgment over raw scanner severity); `semgrep_findings` still reports the raw\n76\tcount of 5, reconciled against the artifact.\n77\t\n78\t## Fixes applied\n79\t\n80\t**#3 — `quotas` RLS tenant-isolation backstop made effective (added `FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY`).**\n81\t`alembic/versions/0003_create_quotas_and_api_key_scope.py`.\n82\t\n83\t- *What was wrong:* the migration enabled `ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` + policy\n84\t  `quotas_tenant_isolation` but not `FORCE`. Alembic resolves its DB URL through the same\n85\t  secrets facade the app uses (`alembic/env.py` → `get_database_url()` → the `meterly_app`\n86\t  credential in Secrets Manager, `infra/modules/data/main.tf:98`), and `meterly_app` holds\n87\t  `CREATE ON SCHEMA public` (`main.tf:83`). The role that runs `CREATE TABLE` **owns** the\n88\t  table, and a table owner **bypasses non-`FORCE` RLS regardless of `NOBYPASSRLS`** — so the\n89\t  backstop policy would be inert for the application role. This is exactly the plan's\n90\t  unresolved Open Question 2. (The infra comment at `main.tf:21-23` asserts the migration job\n91\t  uses the master credential, but the actual `env.py` code path contradicts it and the deploy\n92\t  SSM parameter is an unresolved placeholder — so non-owner cannot be relied on.)\n93\t- *Before:* `ALTER TABLE quotas ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` only.\n94\t- *After:* added `ALTER TABLE quotas FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` (with an explanatory comment).\n95\t  Safe for the app path: every `quotas` access runs inside `scoped_transaction`, which\n96\t  `SET LOCAL app.current_api_key_id`, so the policy's `USING`/`WITH CHECK` predicate passes for\n97\t  the caller's own rows. `FORCE` is dropped implicitly by the `downgrade()` `DROP TABLE`.\n98\t- *Confirmed:* consolidated Semgrep re-scan of the change set after the edit = 0 findings.\n99\t\n100\tNote: this hardens defense-in-depth. The **primary** tenant-isolation control — an explicit\n101\t`api_key_id = :api_key_id` predicate on every `quotas` query — was already present and correct\n102\tin both `upsert_quota` and `read_tenant_quota_state_locked`, so no cross-tenant IDOR was ever\n103\texploitable; finding #3 concerned the second layer, not the barrier.\n104\t\n105\t## Could not remediate\n106\t\n107\tNone.\n108\t\n109\t## Action required (human decision — not auto-fixed)\n110\t\n111\t- **#1 / #2 — `pytest@8.3.4` vulnerable tmpdir handling** (GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g / PYSEC-2026-1845,\n112\t  CVSS ≈ 6.8 Medium). Local-privilege tmpdir predictability in a **dev/test-only** dependency\n113\t  that is not on the request path. Below the deploy gate's CVSS ≥ 7.0 floor → non-blocking.\n114\t  Safe upgrade: bump `pytest` to the patched line (≥ 8.3.5 per the advisory) in `pyproject.toml`\n115\t  + `poetry.lock`. Dependency bumps are the debugging agent's remit, not security's — reported\n116\t  here only.\n117\t\n118\t- **#4 — `events` and `usage_rollup` also lack `FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY`** (pre-existing, from\n119\t  migrations `0001`/`0002`, outside this diff's change set). Same owner-bypass reasoning as #3:\n120\t  their RLS backstops are likely inert for `meterly_app`. Not modified here (out of scope, and\n121\t  the prior `main` security report claimed \"NOBYPASSRLS enforced\" without catching the owner-\n122\t  bypass nuance). **Recommendation:** add `FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` to both tables in a\n123\t  follow-up migration, or verifiably run migrations as `meterly_admin` and confirm `meterly_app`\n124\t  is a non-owner. The explicit `api_key_id` predicate remains the effective primary control on\n125\t  those tables regardless.\n126\t\n127\t## STRIDE mechanism verification (6d)\n128\t\n129\tAll 10 non-accepted-risk threats from `plan.md` §Threat Model have their named mechanism present;\n130\t2 accepted-risk rows (quota-data-at-rest, hot-row serialization latency) skipped per protocol.\n131\t\n132\t| Threat | Mechanism | Evidence | Efficacy |\n133\t|---|---|---|---|\n134\t| Spoofing (non-admin sets cap) | `require_api_key` + admin-scope gate → 403 | `src/api/routes/quotas.py:34-42` | ✓ |\n135\t| Tampering (SQLi) | anchored `constr` allowlist + parameterized `text()` | `src/api/schemas/quotas.py:15-19`, `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py:57-73` | ✓ |\n136\t| Tampering (mass-assignment) | `ConfigDict(extra='forbid')`; server sets `api_key_id` | `src/api/schemas/quotas.py:31`, `src/services/quota_service.py:39-46` | ✓ |\n137\t| Tampering (TOCTOU) | `SELECT … FOR UPDATE` + single `scoped_transaction`; reject before increment | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py:116-149`, `src/services/events_service.py:86-127` | ✓ isolation pinned READ COMMITTED (`src/db/session.py:41`); lock-then-read correct |\n138\t| Repudiation | structured `quota.upsert` / `quota.rejected` | `src/services/quota_service.py:49-56`, `src/services/events_service.py:110-117` | ✓ |\n139\t| Info disclosure | 3-field envelope; logs omit totals | `src/api/errors.py`, `src/services/events_service.py:105-118` | ✓ |\n140\t| DoS (flood) | Tier-2 per-`api_key_id` token bucket on new route | `src/api/routes/quotas.py:34`, `src/auth/rate_limit.py:136-153` | ✓ keyed on `api_key_id`, not IP-behind-ALB |\n141\t| DoS (absurd limit) | `conint(ge=1, le=10**15)` + BIGINT | `src/api/schemas/quotas.py:19` | ✓ |\n142\t| EoP (function-level) | `principal.scope == 'admin'` gate → 403 | `src/api/routes/quotas.py:35-42` | ✓ |\n143\t| EoP (data-level IDOR/BOLA) | explicit `api_key_id` predicate (primary) + RLS backstop | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py:121,136`, migration `0003` | ✓ primary present; RLS backstop made effective via FORCE fix (#3) |\n144\t\n145\t`stride_mechanisms_verified = 10`, `stride_mechanisms_missing = 0`.\n146\t\n147\tEfficacy checks (U-02): **Topology** — Tier-2 throttle keys on `api_key_id` (not client IP), correct\n148\tbehind the ALB. **DB privilege** — owner-bypass gap on `quotas` found and fixed (#3); `events`/\n149\t`usage_rollup` flagged (#4). **Async runtime** — `quotas` access is all `await`ed async DB I/O; no\n150\tCPU-hard KDF on the loop in the new code (Argon2id verify lives in the unchanged auth path).\n151\t**Contract drift** — `customer_id` is in the log redaction set (`src/logging/__init__.py:30`), so the\n152\tnew `quota.*` events honor the redaction contract; the error scrubber path is unchanged.\n153\t\n154\t## STRIDE delta addendum (6f)\n155\t\n156\tNew/changed surface: `PUT /v1/quotas` (entry point), `api_keys.scope` (authz attribute), `quotas`\n157\ttable (data sink). Every one is already covered by a `plan.md` threat-model entry with a verified\n158\tmitigation (see 6d). No new outbound calls, subprocess/exec, SSRF fetch, deserialization, or\n159\tunmodeled data flow. **No STRIDE gap. `stride_new_threats = 0`; addendum empty.**\n160\t\n161\t## ASVS 5.0.0 verification (6g)\n162\t\n163\tTriggered chapters: V1, V2, V4, V6, V8, V12, V13, V14, V15, V16 (per plan `## ASVS Compliance`).\n164\t`n/a`: V3, V5, V7, V9, V10, V11 (no new crypto surface), V17. L1+L2 verified universally; in-scope\n165\tL3 = V15.4.x (TOCTOU-atomic check-then-act) + V11.2.4 (constant-time compare, unchanged).\n166\t\n167\t- V1 parameterized SQL — `text()` bind params only, no interpolation → met.\n168\t- V2 validation / business-logic limit — `constr`/`conint`/`extra='forbid'` → met.\n169\t- V6 API-key auth — Argon2id split-token `require_api_key` (unchanged) → met.\n170\t- V8 authz — function-level admin gate + data-level `api_key_id` scoping (+ RLS backstop now FORCE) → met.\n171\t- V12 TLS — existing ALB/RDS TLS, unchanged → met.\n172\t- V13 config — secrets via Secrets Manager, no hardcoded credentials → met.\n173\t- V14 data protection — identifiers in body not URL; non-sensitive classification → met.\n174\t- V15 secure coding — minimal response fields (`QuotaResponse`), mass-assignment defense, safe concurrency → met.\n175\t- V15.4.x (L3) — `FOR UPDATE` quota-row lock + single-transaction check-then-increment + pinned READ COMMITTED → met.\n176\t- V16 logging/errors — structured logs, PII redaction, generic error envelope → met.\n177\t\n178\t`l1_l2_missing = []`, `l3_in_scope_missing = []`, `doc_advisory = []`, `waivers = []`,\n179\t`reconciled = true`. No plan-cited ASVS mitigation left unimplemented.\n180\t\n181\t## Input-surface reconciliation\n182\t\n183\t1 input source implemented (`PUT /v1/quotas`), 1 declared. Controls present: validation contract\n184\t(`QuotaPutRequest`) + rate-limit policy (Tier-2 per-`api_key_id`). `uncontrolled = []`, reconciled.\n185\t\n186\t## Data-surface reconciliation\n187\t\n188\tStored fields: `quotas.{customer_id, metric, limit_per_window}` + `api_keys.scope` — all classified\n189\t**non-sensitive** operational config/authz metadata per the plan's data-classification table; no\n190\tcredential/sensitive-PII field. At-rest control = RDS SSE (storage-level), no field-level KDF/KMS\n191\trequired. `sensitive = 0`, `unprotected = []`, reconciled.\n192\t\n193\t## Migration scan (`0003`)\n194\t\n195\t- Downgrade path: present (`downgrade()` drops `quotas`, removes `scope` + its CHECK) → not a finding.\n196\t- Destructive ops: `up` is expand-only (create table + add column with backfilling default); `down`'s\n197\t  `DROP TABLE` is the defined reversibility of a create-migration (schema-only, documented) → not a finding.\n198\t- Injectable SQL: none — all static DDL, no user interpolation → not a finding.\n199\t"}]},"uuid":"aba72537-15fb-4188-89ba-a7d034248ebf","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:02:39.985Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"fd545f81-2a16-4631-92b0-0769e29afcec","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"aba72537-15fb-4188-89ba-a7d034248ebf","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a83bffdedaa9ac254","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcqjrcZ4CF3vdcNo1uExG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019rQWb78g9bfk2Ut5HFsGbf","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/src/db/session.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7932,"cache_read_input_tokens":27501,"output_tokens":520,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7932},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":520,"cache_read_input_tokens":27501,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7932,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7932,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccqjrb5kc3Ej16SLmrRD8","attributionAgent":"security","type":"assistant","uuid":"77ad2f3f-5308-4bbe-a8d0-9d07b4ad9bf3","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:02:40.203Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"77ad2f3f-5308-4bbe-a8d0-9d07b4ad9bf3","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ab5f8963-cf84-4410-bcde-8011a87d1e73","agentId":"a83bffdedaa9ac254","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019rQWb78g9bfk2Ut5HFsGbf","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Async database engine/session management.\n2\t\n3\tThe engine is created lazily (on first use / at lifespan startup), never at\n4\timport time — this is what lets `import src.main` succeed in the smoke-check\n5\tbuild-fallback mode with no database reachable. Every request runs inside a\n6\ttransaction that sets `app.current_api_key_id` via `SET LOCAL`, which backs the\n7\tPostgreSQL row-level-security policy on `events`/`usage_rollup` (defense in\n8\tdepth behind the application-level `api_key_id` scoping every repository query\n9\talready applies).\n10\t\"\"\"\n11\t\n12\tfrom collections.abc import AsyncIterator\n13\tfrom contextlib import asynccontextmanager\n14\t\n15\tfrom sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import AsyncEngine, AsyncSession, async_sessionmaker, create_async_engine\n16\t\n17\tfrom src.config.secrets import get_database_url\n18\t\n19\t_engine: AsyncEngine | None = None\n20\t_session_factory: async_sessionmaker[AsyncSession] | None = None\n21\t\n22\t\n23\tdef get_engine() -> AsyncEngine:\n24\t    \"\"\"Return the process-wide async engine, creating it on first call.\n25\t\n26\t    Deferred creation (rather than at import time) keeps `import src.main`\n27\t    dependency-free for the smoke-check build-fallback path.\n28\t    \"\"\"\n29\t    global _engine\n30\t    if _engine is None:\n31\t        _engine = create_async_engine(\n32\t            get_database_url(),\n33\t            # Pin READ COMMITTED explicitly rather than inheriting the DB/role\n34\t            # default. quotas_repo.read_tenant_quota_state_locked locks the\n35\t            # quotas row (SELECT ... FOR UPDATE) then reads usage_rollup in a\n36\t            # SEPARATE statement; that read only sees the prior lock holder's\n37\t            # committed increment because each statement gets a fresh snapshot\n38\t            # under READ COMMITTED. Under REPEATABLE READ a lock-waiter would\n39\t            # read a stale rollup total and admit events past the quota cap\n40\t            # (see the read_tenant_quota_state_locked docstring).\n41\t            isolation_level=\"READ COMMITTED\",\n42\t            pool_pre_ping=True,\n43\t            pool_size=10,\n44\t            max_overflow=5,\n45\t        )\n46\t    return _engine\n47\t\n48\t\n49\tdef get_session_factory() -> async_sessionmaker[AsyncSession]:\n50\t    \"\"\"Return the process-wide session factory, creating it on first call.\"\"\"\n51\t    global _session_factory\n52\t    if _session_factory is None:\n53\t        _session_factory = async_sessionmaker(get_engine(), expire_on_commit=False)\n54\t    return _session_factory\n55\t\n56\t\n57\t@asynccontextmanager\n58\tasync def scoped_transaction(api_key_id: int) -> AsyncIterator[AsyncSession]:\n59\t    \"\"\"Open a transaction scoped to the authenticated `api_key_id`.\n60\t\n61\t    Sets `app.current_api_key_id` with `SET LOCAL` at the start of the\n62\t    transaction so the PostgreSQL RLS policy backstop applies even if a\n63\t    repository query were ever missing its own `api_key_id` filter. The\n64\t    setting is transaction-local and is discarded automatically on commit/\n65\t    rollback.\n66\t    \"\"\"\n67\t    session_factory = get_session_factory()\n68\t    async with session_factory() as session, session.begin():\n69\t        await session.execute(\n70\t            _set_local_statement(),\n71\t            {\"api_key_id\": str(api_key_id)},\n72\t        )\n73\t        yield session\n74\t\n75\t\n76\tdef _set_local_statement():\n77\t    \"\"\"Build the `SET LOCAL` statement for the current-tenant RLS setting.\n78\t\n79\t    A separate function keeps the (slightly unusual) `set_config` call —\n80\t    `SET LOCAL` does not accept a bound parameter directly in all drivers —\n81\t    isolated and documented in one place.\n82\t    \"\"\"\n83\t    from sqlalchemy import text\n84\t\n85\t    return text(\"SELECT set_config('app.current_api_key_id', :api_key_id, true)\")\n86\t\n87\t\n88\tasync def dispose_engine() -> None:\n89\t    \"\"\"Dispose of the engine's connection pool (called from lifespan shutdown).\"\"\"\n90\t    global _engine, _session_factory\n91\t    if _engine is not None:\n92\t        await _engine.dispose()\n93\t    _engine = None\n94\t    _session_factory = None\n95\t\n96\t\n97\tasync def check_database_ready() -> bool:\n98\t    \"\"\"Run a fast `SELECT 1` to back the `/health/ready` readiness probe.\"\"\"\n99\t    from sqlalchemy import text\n100\t\n101\t    try:\n102\t        async with get_engine().connect() as connection:\n103\t            await connection.execute(text(\"SELECT 1\"))\n104\t        return True\n105\t    except Exception:  # noqa: BLE001 - readiness must never raise, only report False\n106\t        return False\n107\t"}]},"uuid":"e60df3aa-f612-4a28-bf3b-b4db1008b788","timestamp":"2026-07-09T03:02:40.231Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"77ad2f3f-5308-4bbe-a8d0-9d07b4ad9bf3","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
